**CLAUSE 1: PRICE VOLATILITY AND CONTRACT RENEGOTIATION**

1.1 The Parties agree that in the event of a material change in market conditions, including but not limited to, a 15% increase in the global cobalt price as reported by the London Metal Exchange (LME) over a 30-day period, the Purchaser shall have the right to request renegotiation of the Contract Price.

1.2 For the purposes of this Clause, a "material change in market conditions" shall be deemed to have occurred if the global cobalt price exceeds USD 80,000 per tonne for a period of 30 consecutive days.

1.3 In the event of a request for renegotiation, the Parties shall engage in good faith negotiations to agree on a revised Contract Price, taking into account the changed market conditions.

1.4 If the Parties are unable to agree on a revised Contract Price within 60 days of the request, the Purchaser shall have the right to terminate this Contract with immediate effect.

**CLAUSE 2: FORCE MAJEURE CONDITIONS**

2.1 For the purposes of this Contract, a "Force Majeure Event" shall mean any event or circumstance beyond the reasonable control of the Supplier, including but not limited to:

(a) Natural disasters, including but not limited to, earthquakes, hurricanes, floods, and droughts;

(b) Governmental actions, including but not limited to, embargoes, sanctions, and changes in laws or regulations;

(c) Wars, terrorism, and civil unrest;

(d) Strikes, lockouts, and other industrial disputes;

(e) Epidemics, pandemics, and other public health crises;

(f) Cyber-attacks and other forms of cyber-terrorism;

(g) Supply chain disruptions, including but not limited to, the failure of key suppliers or transportation providers.

2.2 In the event of a Force Majeure Event, the Supplier shall notify the Purchaser in writing within 5 days of the occurrence of the event.

2.3 The Supplier shall use its best efforts to mitigate the effects of the Force Majeure Event and to restore normal supply as soon as possible.

2.4 If the Force Majeure Event continues for a period of 90 days or more, the Purchaser shall have the right to terminate this Contract with immediate effect.

**CLAUSE 3: SUSTAINABILITY AND ENVIRONMENTAL COMPLIANCE**

3.1 The Supplier warrants that it shall comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and industry standards related to sustainability and environmental protection, including but not limited to:

(a) The OECD Due Diligence Guidance for Responsible Supply Chains of Minerals from Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Areas;

(b) The International Cyanide Management Code;

(c) The Extractive Industries Transparency Initiative (EITI);

(d) The International Labour Organization (ILO) Core Conventions.

3.2 The Supplier shall maintain a robust and transparent system of governance, including but not limited to, a Code of Conduct and a system of internal controls, to ensure compliance with the requirements set out in this Clause.

3.3 The Supplier shall provide the Purchaser with regular reports on its sustainability and environmental performance, including but not limited to, its progress in implementing the requirements set out in this Clause.

3.4 The Purchaser reserves the right to audit the Supplier's sustainability and environmental performance at any time during the term of this Contract.

**CLAUSE 4: SUPPLIER RESPONSIBILITY**

4.1 The Supplier warrants that it shall be responsible for all aspects of the supply chain, including but not limited to:

(a) The sourcing of cobalt from reputable suppliers;

(b) The transportation of cobalt to the Purchaser;

(c) The storage and handling of cobalt at the Purchaser's premises.

4.2 The Supplier shall maintain a robust system of internal controls to ensure compliance with the requirements set out in this Clause.

4.3 The Supplier shall provide the Purchaser with regular reports on its supply chain performance, including but not limited to, its progress in implementing the requirements set out in this Clause.

4.4 The Purchaser reserves the right to audit the Supplier's supply chain performance at any time during the term of this Contract.

